2026-05-17 05:08:45 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #7 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"intent": "Compute Pearson correlation between annual (NOAA-NIFC) differences for number of fires and acres burned. Aggregate NOAA monthly data to annual totals, align with NIFC annual data, compute differences, then correlation.", "code": "import pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\n\nnoaa_path = 'kramabench-wildfire-hard-6/files/noaa_wildfires_monthly_stats.csv'\nnifc_path = 'kramabench-wildfire-hard-6/files/nifc_wildfires.csv'\n\n# Load NOAA monthly\nnoaa = pd.read_csv(noaa_path)\n# Columns: Date, Acres Burned, Number of Fires, Acres Burned per Fire\n# Date format like 200001 (YYYYMM)\nnoaa['Year'] = (noaa['Date'].astype(str).str[:4]).astype(int)\nnoaa_annual = noaa.groupby('Year', as_index=False).agg({\n    'Acres Burned':'sum',\n    'Number of Fires':'sum'\n})\n\n# Load NIFC annual\nnifc = pd.read_csv(nifc_path, sep='\\t')\n# Columns: Year, Fires, Acres\nnifc_annual = nifc.rename(columns={'Fires':'Number of Fires','Acres':'Acres Burned'})\n\n# Merge on Year\nm = pd.merge(noaa_annual, nifc_annual[['Year','Number of Fires','Acres Burned']], on='Year', how='inner', suffixes=('_NOAA','_NIFC'))\n\n# Differences\nm['diff_fires'] = m['Number of Fires_NOAA'] - m['Number of Fires_NIFC']\nm['diff_acres'] = m['Acres Burned_NOAA'] - m['Acres Burned_NIFC']\n\n# Pearson correlation\ncorr = m['diff_fires'].corr(m['diff_acres'])\n\nprint(corr)\nprint(len(m))\nprint(m[['Year','diff_fires','diff_acres']].head())\n", "dataset_id": "kramabench-wildfire-hard-6"}) [toolUseId=call_xKBNpakzFQJixttXAfa5mqFH]
